  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Lab Technician",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Main Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><p>·Compound standard and repeat samples</p><p>·Samples preparation for submissions and evaluations</p><p>· Lab management, ensure smooth & efficient lab operations</p><p>· Upkeep and maintain raw materials library</p><p>· Ensure raw materials and samples meet quality standards which include day to day evaluations</p><p>· Keep proper documentations and updates of data in Technical Workbench</p><p>· Implement and adhered to all established Lab practices, quality, safety and environmental management policy</p><p>· Conduct tests according to project needs</p><p>· Monitor laboratory equipment & facilities, raise purchase orders or work orders when required</p><p>· Samples despatch to affiliates and customers</p><p>· Carry out any additional job-related duties as and when necessary</p><p><br /></p><p><u><strong>Functional Skills & Competencies:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Good interpersonal skills.</li><li>Possess high Emotional Quotient</li><li>Able to work independently and a good team player</li><li>Good personal conduct and positive working attitude</li><li>Able to handle urgent requests with priorities</li></ul><p><u>Primary Qualification:</u></p><ul><li>Higher NITEC / Diploma in Food Science or equivalent in years of similar experience</li><li>No colour blindness</li><li>No allergy to scent and able to tolerate strong smells</li></ul>",
